 again - she said to - I want a - a light dress. And mother used to go and buy - the material you see in those days, the - there wasn't many - much made up stuff in those days. And mother brought this dark material. Oh and I was really disgusted. I said, 
I
 wanted a light dress for a change. And Mrs. - Rhodes - she said, do you know, she says, if I was your mother I'd put you in black, she said. She said, you're the most dirty little madam I ever did see. She says, you're never clean, she says, your mother 
g
oes to al this trouble to get - to get you these nice dresses, and pinafores, we used to have the pinafores with the - embroider round and the lace round, and - but - I was - I was a - a real tomboy, you know, I - I was never clean mother said, it didn't 
